  "text": "In these two equations Z i→j and Z i are both normalizing constants determined by the constraints Notice that each of the O(N 2 ) message equations in (101) contains N − 1 terms, meaning that each iteration of the BP equations requires O(N 3 ) computation. For sparse graphs the following heuristic approximation dramatically simplifies the computation [CITATION_1] . We first separate the product in (101) into neighbor nodes (k ∈ ∂i) and non-neighbor nodes (k / ∈ ∂i):",
